Flycheck is a modern alternative to Flymake that supports many programming languages out of the box. It is available [https://github.com/flycheck/flycheck on GitHub].

== JSLint with Flycheck ==

As of mid September 2013, Flycheck has no built in support for JSLint. Fortunately support is straight forward to add.

1. Install [http://nodejs.org/ Node.js].

2. Install [https://github.com/FND/jslint-reporter jslint-reporter] into: <code>~/.emacs.d/jslint-reporter</code>

3. Download JSLint (or JSHint, using <code>--jshint</code>):

<pre>
$ cd ~/.emacs.d/jslint-reporter
$ node wrapper.js --upgrade
</pre>

4. Create an executable script:

* UNIX, <code>~/.emacs.d/jslint-reporter.sh</code>:

<pre>
#!/bin/sh
node "`dirname \"$0\"`/jslint-reporter/wrapper.js" "$@"
</pre>

* Windows, <code>~/.emacs.d/jslint-reporter.js</code> (temp file is a [http://stackoverflow.com/questions/18748164/process-exit0-output-disappears workaround]):

<pre>
@ECHO OFF
node c:\Temp\jslint-reporter-master\jslint-reporter-master\wrapper.js >"%TEMP%"\jslint-reporter.out 2>&1 %*
TYPE "%TEMP%"\jslint-reporter.out
</pre>

5. Create a test file <code>test.js</code>:

<pre>
// Test
console.log("Hello world!");
</pre>

6. From EShell (CategoryEshell) test jslint-reporter <em>(on Windows replace <code>.sh</code> with <code>.bat</code>):</em>

<pre>
$ ~/.emacs.d/jslint-reporter.bat test.js
test.js:2:1:'console' was used before it was defined.
</pre>

7. Install [https://github.com/flycheck/flycheck Flycheck].

8. Add to <code>~/.emacs</code> <em>(on Windows replace <code>.sh</code> with <code>.bat</code>):</em>

<pre>
(require 'flycheck)
(flycheck-define-checker javascript-jslint-reporter
  "A JavaScript syntax and style checker based on using JSLint Reporter.

See URL `https://github.com/FND/jslint-reporter'."
  :command ("~/.emacs.d/jslint-reporter.sh" source)
  :error-patterns
  ((error line-start (1+ nonl) ":" line ":" column ":" (message) line-end))
  :modes (js-mode js2-mode js3-mode))
(add-hook 'js-mode-hook (lambda ()
                          (flycheck-select-checker 'javascript-jslint-reporter)
                          (flycheck-mode)))
</pre>

9. Restart Emacs to make sure everything loads fine.

10. Test by opening above <code>test.js</code>.

